25/01/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik says he expects a law on referendums to be passed by the entity's parliament in February.
Dodik was in Belgrade on Saturday (January 23rd) attending the ceremony to enthrone Bishop Irinej of Nis as the new patriarch of the Serbian Orthodox Church.
Dodik said that once the measure on referendums is passed, RS citizens are expected to vote on whether they support the 1995 Dayton Agreement that ended the Bosnian conflict.
He did not specify the exact timing of the referendum.
(RTRS, Srna, Tanjug - 23/01/10)
